caption: The food was good, I didn't like that the waiter came to us with the bill and told my wife to do a review and write his name in the recommendation while he didn't even serve our table.

Danmarkshuset - The Denmark House - was the setting for a 2-day course attended by participants from schools in Denmark and the EU. Lovely conditions right on Avenue des Champs-Élysées allowed for dining and refreshments during breaks and after the course program. The large hall on the 2nd floor of Denmark House served well as a meeting room and conference space.
Very nice and unexpected place among the many uninteresting shops on Champs Élysées avenue. Flora Danica is also a nice bar/ restaurant. The exhibition for the Olympics was very well done.

A charming spot, but La Maison du Danemark on the Champs-Élysées feels oppressive for climate and ocean advocates like Captain Paul Watson. Unexpectedly, Denmark appears to muzzle environmental voices in a way reminiscent of China. It's disappointing that beneath the beauty lies a link to such distressing measures.
Beautiful salmon and herring tasting platters and the fish was so fresh. Highly recommend. I used the website and booked twenty minutes in advance. No trouble getting seated at lunchtime
They gave out free food and drinks. And it gave alot of information about Denmark and it looked really good

We went to the restaurant for a brunch. The brunch buffet contains a great variety of food, including vegetarian options. The setting is comfortable , we were a group of 6 and we were quite comfortable in the table setting. The design is modern and elegant. What did not went well was the quality of service. The staff were in a hurry, no time to listen to the customers, mistakes in bringing the required food / drinks etc. The atmosphere could be much more pleasant, including a better contact between the staff and the customers. This is the main thing to work on.

Don't really understand the thing about this house except for that it is very fancy and I really recommend going there.  Go to the terrasse and enjoy the view of the view over the world famous street of champs-élysées.

I was there to visit the exposition on 2nd floor. Apparently no one knows when does it open! The restaurant on the first floor told me it’ll be open at 13h, so I waited there until the other person who works from upstairs told me it’ll be open next week or after next week!! On the website it is written open at 12h! Really bad organization!
didnt wait too long to be able to go in tbh we went early in the morning
Good taste and association. They've revamped their whole menu with all the recent changes. It was the first time trying on Caviar. As a seafood lover, this was exquisite and well balanced.

Just okay, it could be better. I had the avocado toast that wasn't toasted and had very little avocado for 14 Euros. The alcoholic drinks were okay but it seemed like the Parisians had a larger glass than the foreigners, for the same drink and price. A pleasant place to sit close to the Arch de Triumph, if you don't care about these things. Of course, it is on the Champs Elysees, that counts for something.
Excellent,  food , service and very chic inside compared to the outside tables.
Location in the back garden was fantastic, food and service average for this level of establishment.
Well. The view to the environment is good. But not the same anymore. Sadly.
Fantastic food and service. Great dishes really original and full of unknown and delicious flavors!
Great food and service. Located back off of the street, but lovely. Striking Danish modern decor. Recommend.
Great food and wine, with excellent service.
